<L>__{interior friendship moments later}
<A>__{with amelia as she locks the hatch. for the first time, we can see the inside of the plane. the cabin is too small for anyone to stand. the plane has been emptied of everything but two huge elliptical fuel tanks. she wedges herself between the gigantic tanks. bill pulls the throttle and the fokker tri motor lurches forward, straining against the surface of the sea in a rattling, throbbing desperately vibrating all out attempt. amelia crawls to the tiny window, her face to the glass as chop and spray fly past like shrapnel, and the engines whine and pulse louder... ...twenty seconds, thirty. still on the surface. forty seconds, fifty, her eyes shut, her forehead bangs against the glass, come on, sixty seconds, and at 67...}
